The positions and motions of the electrolyte atoms are described normally as functions of boundary nodes with certain changes. Consequently, the electrolyte molecules come across each other, and the molecules on the graphene surface may switch to a different route at each time step48. It is rather difficult to monitor the movements of electrolyte molecules in real time, because each molecule’s path along the time is rather random and rather uneven49. The displacement travelled by molecules can be calculated with the help of MSD of electrolyte molecules. The MSD of a molecule is obtained based on current position with respect to time50,51. From the work of Bian et al.52, Eq. 5 can be interpreted as the average MSD for many electrolyte molecules available.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
